<h3>Image Requirements</h3>
<p>Google requires at least 1 image in Article schema. The image must be at least 50,000 pixels (for example, 250x200).</p>
<p>Provide 3 aspect ratios for maximum rich result coverage: 16:9, 4:3, and 1:1. Google selects the best fit for each SERP placement. Failing to provide multiple sizes means Google may crop your image poorly or skip it.</p>
<h3>Author Best Practices</h3>
<p>Separate the author into its own <code>@type: Person</code> object. Do not use a plain text string.</p>
<p>Include <code>sameAs</code> links to the author's LinkedIn, Twitter, or personal website. Add <code>knowsAbout</code> to list the author's areas of expertise. These properties feed directly into Google's E-E-A-T evaluation and AI citation confidence scoring.</p>
<p>Never use generic author names like "Admin," "Staff," or "Editorial Team" without also providing a <code>url</code> pointing to a real about page. Google discounts anonymous authors for E-E-A-T purposes.</p>
